H0.text: Carbon chains form the skeletons of most organic molecules.

H1.text: Hydrocarbons form the skeletons of most organic molecules.

H2.text: Amino acid chains form the skeletons of most organic molecules.

H3.text: Peptide groups form the skeletons of most organic molecules.

A4.text: An unlabeled vertex is understood to represent a carbon attached to the number of hydrogens required to satisfy the octet rule

A5.text: The skeleton can consist of chains, branches and/or rings of bonded atoms
